added.title: Crab Shenanigans
added.description: Beast Boy, Negative Girl, and Robotman start hanging out with some punk crabs but soon discover the crabs are up to no good.

added.title: We're Off to Get Awards
added.description: During an awards ceremony, Robin is swept up by a tornado and arrives in a magical land.

added.title: Walk Away
added.description: After the T-Car is destroyed in a fight, the Titans go to a used car lot to find another vehicle.

added.title: Record Book
added.description: Starfire wants a world record, so she decides to grow her fingernails.

added.title: Titans Go Casual
added.description: The Superhero Board of Authority institutes a dress code which leads the Titans to introduce Casual Tuesday.

added.title: Teen Titans Roar!
added.description: The Titans are outraged when their favorite cartoon is rebooted so they come up with a plan to get this new show off the air.

added.title: Girls Night In Part 1
added.description: The Girls Night Out Crew decide to stay in and have a slumber party but an unknown alien threat descends on Jump City.

added.title: Girls Night In Part 2
added.description: When Blackfire begins her plan to conquer Earth, the girls must pull out all the stops to defeat her.

added.title: The Great Disaster
added.description: Robin gets amnesia and starts thinking that Hawkman is his mother.

added.title: Two Parter Part 1
added.description: The Titans visit the Hall of Justice to use the pool, but then decide to check out the inside.

added.title: Two Parter Part 2
added.description: The Titans must save the members of the Justice League from the clutches of the supervillain Darkseid.

added.title: Operation Dude Rescue Part 1
added.description: When the male Titans are captured, it's up to Starfire and Raven to rescue them but they're going to need some extra girl power.

added.title: Operation Dude Rescue Part 2
added.description: Female heroes and villains unite to save Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy from The Brain.

added.title: Man Person
added.description: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.

added.title: Subway
added.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

added.title: Panda's Friend
added.description: Panda uses an app to find a friend with whom he has more common with. Soon things take a turn for the worse when the new friend gets too possessive.

added.title: Neighbors
added.description: Some new neighbors set up camp next to the Bears' cave. Panda and Ice love it, but Grizz thinks they're up to no good.

added.title: Planet Bears
added.description: A nature documentary follows the Bears through their normal routine, which includes a trip to the grocery store.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Creature Mysteries
added.description: Ranger Tabes tells the Bears she's been investigating a mysterious creature. But when the Bears realize she's actually investigating their friend Charlie, they split up to ensure Charlie's safety.

added.title: Grizz Helps
added.description: When his brothers don't need his help for the day, Grizz leaves the cave to assist anyone he can throughout the city.

added.title: Grizzly the Movie
added.description: Grizz gets cast in a movie about a Grizzly Bear! But Grizz soon realizes the movie's depiction of grizzly bears is not what he had in mind.

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: The Pact
added.description: Gumball finds Penny's laugh annoying, but can't think of a way to tell her without offending her. When he discovers that Principal Brown has the same problem with Miss Simian's morning breath, they decide to swap problems to save themselves from getting dumped.

added.title: The Ollie
added.description: When Darwin asks Gumball to teach him how to skate, Gumball makes sure he covers every aspect of the skating lifestyle from wearing the right gear, using the right terms and choosing the right board. But when Darwin finally gets his wheels rolling, he realizes there might be one important aspect of skating Gumball hasn't taught him.

added.title: The Nuisance
added.description: The Wattersons fear the worst when they are summoned to a Town Hall meeting, but are pleasantly surprised when they're offered a brand new house.  Until they discover it's in a different state! The Mayor of Elmore has decided they are bringing down the real estate value of the entire town so the family have to prove that they're upstanding members of the community.

added.title: The Origins
added.description: When Mom and Dad struggle to keep hyperactive, toddler-aged Gumball from trashing the house and exhausting them, they decide to buy him a pet. It works, but there's a problem: every goldfish they get him is short-lived, and inevitably ends up being flushed down the toilet.

added.title: The Origins Part 2
added.description: Via the sewers, Darwin finds himself flushed out to sea. He is terrified but determined to make his way back to the Wattersons. However, a fish can't get very far on land so Darwin will have to do millions of years of evolution in a matter of hours if he's going to get home safe and sound.

added.title: The Night
added.description: As night falls in Elmore, the Moon takes us on a tour through the various dreams and nightmares of the town's slumbering inhabitants. Each character's dream shows us their innermost desires, their greatest fears or just how plain weird they are.

added.title: The Oracle
added.description: Banana Barbara has made a prophecy which Gumball simply cannot accept. Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Banana Joe's mom paints pictures which predict the future. When they find one that depicts Gumball running naked through the mall, Gumball is determined not to let it come to pass. However events conspire against him, and Gumball learns that sometimes you can't fight fate.

added.title: The Nobody
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover they have an uninvited house guest. Things keep going missing in the house, so it's up to Gumball and Darwin to find the culprit. They discover that a mysterious person has been secretly living in their home. Gumball and Darwin manage to turn this confused squatter into their mortal enemy . . .

added.title: The Knights
added.description: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

added.title: The Quest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Anais rescue her doll from Tina Rex.

added.title: The Painting
added.description: Principal Brown tries to "fix" Gumball's dysfunctional family.

added.title: The Prank
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's harmless pranks on Dad spiral hopelessly out of control.

added.title: The Party
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are invited to a high school party, and have to bring a date!

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: The Poltergeist
added.description: Gumball and Darwin give Mr Robinson a home and end up saving his marriage.

added.title: Xingo's World
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max are on the road again and are supposed to be taking in the beautiful sights, but Ben refuses to put his video games away. Only the unexpected return of Xingo can spur him into action and teach him that the real world is just as important as any virtual one!

added.title: Tummy Ache
added.description: Team Tennyson go on a tour of the new Biggie Box Candy Store, but when Toothache breaks out and kidnaps the owner, Mr. Biggie, it is up to Ben to stop the monstrous dentist and save the candy man and his wondrous candy store.

added.title: Players of the Lost Park
added.description: When Team Tennyson visits Raspberry Park for some R & R, they get more than they bargained for. What they think are innocent games of chance are a revenge plot by Zombozo to steal the Rustbuggy and rob Team Tennyson!

added.title: De-Fanged!
added.description: Team Tennyson travels to the new Laser Town VR, but when Kevin cheats his way to the top, Ben must team up with former champ Fang if he is going to defeat his souped-up rival.

added.title: Mock 10
added.description: Ben, Kevin and La Grange find themselves stuck 'outside of time' after the latter hijacks a supersonic train with a faulty engine, forcing the trio to team up and slow down.

added.title: Rekoil
added.description: As Team Tennyson fights to stop Dr. Animo from raiding an animal shelter, Ben faces one villain more than he bargained for, King Koil, now Animo's pet.

added.title: Buktu The Future
added.description: After Tim Buktu's live stream is mysteriously cut short, Team Tennyson must attempt a rescue mission and break inside the highly confidential Area 55 in order to save him.

added.title: Ben 10,010
added.description: In a future where an adult Gwen Tennyson is president and the world is being taken over by the alien horde known as the Xerge, a disillusioned Ben 10000 is called out of retirement to recruit his 10-year old version from the past - only together can the battle-worn adult and the impulsive child save a future under siege.

added.title: Ben Gen 10
added.description: When Ben meets a young Generator Rex on the run from a hostile Providence, he must work through a series of misunderstandings, and defeat the dark wizard Hex in order to save the world from a malfunctioning Omnitrix infecting the world's human population with alien DNA.

added.title: Alien X-Tinction
added.description: When the Tennysons are attacked by a villainous, dimension-hopping Omni-alien known only as Alien X, they soon meet a parallel universe version of Max who opens the door to hosting multiple Bens and Gwens, forming an alien hero army to combat this threat.

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Double Hex
added.description: While bird watching at Pinnacles National Park, Gwen and Ben get into a competition of who can spot more birds first, but once a forest fire interrupts their fun, Team Tennyson must hurry if they are to save the bird population and discover who is behind the suspiciously growing fire: Hex!

added.title: Ben Again and Again
added.description: After Billy Billions' efforts to carve his face onto Mount Rushmore with a laser are thwarted by Ben, the billionaire brat turns his focus on removing Ben from the Omnitrix, but once he accidentally rips open a rift in space-time, the two must carefully navigate another timeline if they are to return to the present.

added.title: Drone On
added.description: Ben and Gwen are in a highly competitive paper airplane war, but when alien-tech drones bombard the Rustbucket, the cousins must work together to ground the aerial attack and find out who's behind it: the alien conqueror, Vilgax!

added.title: Dreamtime
added.description: After a series of reoccurring nightmares affect his sleep, Ben refuses to open up to Max and Gwen about what's bothering him, but once they realize Zombozo himself is behind it, Ben must accept Max and Gwen's help if they are going to put a stop to the terror.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a funny formula that will land him a comedic in a movie.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple & Onion try to finish a story before the book disappears forever.

added.title: Appleoni
added.description: Apple and Onion want credit for creating a new dance craze.

added.title: Falafel's in Jail
added.description: Apple & Onion must get Falafel out of jail for a crime he did not commit.

added.title: The Music Store Thief
added.description: Apple and Onion have to defend the music store from instrument theft to get a key to the store.

added.title: The Fly
added.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

added.title: Dragonhead
added.description: Apple and Onion must run a secret parking lot on their roof terrace so they can have a shower.

added.title: Pulling Your Weight
added.description: Apple and Onion join a gym to gain the strength of seven people.

added.title: Rotten Apple
added.description: Apple and Onion try to convince Onion's Dad that Apple is not a bad influence.

added.title: The Inbetween
added.description: Apple and Onion get lost beneath their floorboards and must find a way out.

added.title: The Guest
added.description: Vic & Val blame each other for eating all the food in the kitchen and making a huge mess! However, they soon discover that a ghost is actually to blame! They enlist the help of Achi to unlock the world of spirits among them and kick the ghost out of their house!

added.title: Ener-G-Shoes
added.description: When Vic uses trickery to buy a pair of super cool sneakers from Maria Teresa's yard sale, the shoes try to walk him to his demise as punishment.

added.title: La Cucarachita
added.description: When Vic's beloved pet cockroach dies, Vic turns to Charlene's dark magic to bring her back to life.

added.title: Lords of Ghost Town
added.description: When V&V recruit a ghost to scare away a bully, they end up messing with the realm of the dead, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: My Fair Achi
added.description: V&V enter Achi in a dog show competition to win a golden trophy, but their overbearing ways drive Achi to the edge.

added.title: The Dark Room
added.description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

added.title: The Collector
added.description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: With many changes going on in his life, Steven tries to find his place in the world.

added.title: Together Alone
added.description: Steven throws a party to bring his family together.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Cat Fingers
added.description: Steven attempts to master the power of shape shifting, but can only shape shift his fingers into tiny cat heads.

added.title: Serious Steven
added.description: Steven tries to prove himself to be a worthy Crystal Gem to Garnet while they navigate their way out of an ancient Gem maze.

added.title: Steven's Lion
added.description: Steven makes friends with a magical lion, but can't quite tell why it likes him.

added.title: Giant Woman
added.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

added.title: Sick Mao
added.description: When Mao Mao won't admit that he's sick, he puts the town in danger.

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.

added.title: Small
added.description: Mao Mao's legendary, gigantic and critical father visits his son at his new job as sheriff.

added.title: Legend of Torbaclaun
added.description: When the Sweetypies think the mythical Torbaclaun has come to Pure Heart Valley, Mao Mao tries to prove to them that it isn't real.

added.title: Meet Tanya Keys
added.description: When bounty hunter Tanya Keys comes to town for Badgerclops, it's up to Mao Mao and Adorabat to save their friend -- even if he's been on the wrong side of the law.

added.title: Weapon of Choice
added.description: Worried that his sword is a glorified consolation prize, Mao Mao sets out to prove the worth of his weapon.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: When they think each others' lives are easier, the heroes switch roles.

added.title: Morituri Te Salutamus
added.description: Finn and Jake are trapped in the arena of the Fight King and must face gladiators to set themselves free.

added.title: Adventure Time with Fionna and Cake
added.description: It's a parallel universe where we explore the adventures of Fiona and Cake from the land of Aaa!

added.title: Apple Thief
added.description: Finn and Jake are feeling peckish and only one thing can satisfy their hunger: Tree Trunks' world-famous apple pie!

added.title: From Bad to Worse
added.description: A zombie epidemic strikes in Ooo and it's Princess Bubblegum's fault.

added.title: Ghost Princess
added.description: Finn and Jake try to solve Ghost Princess' unsolved murder.

added.title: Power Animal
added.description: Finn is kidnapped by a group of gnomes, who want to harness his energy to take over the world. Only Jake can save his best friend if he can just focus long enough to follow the obvious clues and rescue Finn.

added.title: Death in Bloom
added.description: Finn and Jake are terrible house sitters and have to go on a quest to replace Princess Bubblegum's rare flower.

added.title: Mystery Train
added.description: Finn and Jake get wrapped up in a high speed whodunit!

added.title: Mortal Folly
added.description: Finn and Jake hunt down the evil Lich King while the Ice King pesters them for their approval to date Princess Bubblegum.

added.title: Mortal Recoil
added.description: Doctor Princess brings Princess Bubblegum back from the brink of death, but is she really herself?

added.title: Slumber Party Panic
added.description: Finn must keep his promise to Princess Bubblegum and cover up the zombie problem they've created.

added.title: My Two Favorite People
added.description: Jake tries to broker peace between Rainicorn and Finn.

added.title: Ocean of Fear
added.description: Finn faces his biggest challenge yet, overcoming his fear of water.

added.title: Henchman
added.description: While trying to rescue a helpless stranger, Finn becomes Marceline's slave.

added.title: Rainy Day Daydream
added.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.

added.title: Wiener Club
added.description: Puppycorn is determined to become the Hot Dog King and joins an underground hot dog eating contest called Weiner Club. Rick warns "you are what you eat," but Puppycorn doesn't listen and eats so many hot dogs he becomes the new champion of Weiner Club. Unfortunately he also literally turns into a hot dog, that the other club members reveal they are going to eat! Unikitty and the gang now must attack with vegetables and defeat the hot dog-eating baddies in order to save the giant hot-dog-shaped Puppycorn and turn him back to normal.

added.title: Trapped in the Tower
added.description: During a fun fireworks show, Unikitty and Master Frown become trapped in the horn of the Unikitty Castle when she catches Master Frown messing with her fireworks. Unikitty takes this as an opportunity to figure out why Master Frown is always such a Cranky McCrabby Face all the time, if only Master Frown would let his emotional guard down! She tries all kinds of tactics, a song, a dance, even a firework with a face drawn on it named "Professor Pow Pow, licensed therapist" Getting nowhere, Unikitty ends up raging out and setting the tower and all the fireworks alight. In desperation to not burn alive, Master Frown tells Unikitty a story about a younger Master Frown who was gifted a special lollipop but after a freak chain of events, was broken right before his eyes. Unikitty cries her eyes out and puts out the fires and then reveals it was her plan all along to get Master Frown to talk about his feelings!

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: After being rudely interrupted by Bim Bom during her daily morning song, an angry Unikitty takes the advice of her friends and writes down her feelings into a letter with the intention of keeping the letter to herself, but then accidentally sends it off, complete with postage! The gang then goes on a wild chase through the Unikingdom mail delivery service to keep that rude letter from getting into the hands of Bim Bom, and ultimately hurting her feelings. Turns out, Unikitty's "rude" is everyone else's "nice" and the letter was full of compliments.

added.title: Scary Tales 2
added.description: It's Halloween again and the gang is desperately trying to tell the scariest story to a couple of trick or treaters. Each of the characters takes turns adding onto the last story, going through a haunted glove to a haunted action figure to haunted everything, and even a spooky song! None work in scaring the kids when suddenly a full scale alien invasion happens right before their eyes! Still, the trick or treaters are unimpressed until Richard takes the story stage and delivers a story no kid wants to hear- instead of candy, the trick or treaters would get granola bars! The kids, and Puppycorn, run away screaming.

added.title: Old Lady Bodyguard
added.description: After being "bought" at a charity auction, Hawkodile is forced to spend the day as Old Lady Edith's personal bodyguard.

added.title: Perfect Moment
added.description: When Hawkodile admits his love for Dr. Fox, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings for her. Unfortunately, Unikitty's grand plans for the perfect moment of love complicates everything.

added.title: Hawkodile Sensei
added.description: On a routine mission, Hawkodile finds some defenseless chipmunks that imprint on him.​ ​The bird bodyguard takes it upon himself to become their Sensei teach the younglings his warrior ways, but Unikitty worries his training is too intense. Will Hawkodile's "all work, no play" lifestyle push the chipmunks too far?

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device
added.description: When boredom levels in the castle hit dangerously high levels, Dr. Fox conveniently introduces her P.L.O.T. Device. When pressed, this device alters reality to make it more exciting. Richard warns that this might be dangerous, but no one listens. It's not long till he is proven correct and life in the castle becomes dangerously exciting.

added.title: Beep
added.description: To help combat bummer feelings, Unikitty's installed Bad Vibe detectors throughout the castle. But soon, annoying beeping detectors fill the halls, and they can't find the source of the bad vibes or shut off the sound! It would seem someone's not owning up to being in a bad mood.Will the friends figure out who is secretly a Negative Nancy, or will they lose their mind to beeping madness?

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: When the Score creeper traps Unikitty and the gang in his laser tag arena the gang must defeat the house team or be imprisoned forever.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Birthday Blowout
added.description: Puppycorn's birthday wish is stolen by Master Frown, the biggest downer in the kingdom! To recover it, Unikitty and Puppycorn will have to venture into the most depressing land ever, Frown Town! Will they manage to recover the birthday wish from Frown before his wish (and all wishes) are wished away forever?

added.title: Landlord Lord
added.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

added.title: Scary Tales
added.description: During the gang's Halloween party, Unikitty discovers Brick isn't scared of anything! To get him in the holiday spirit, the gang tell their own ideas of what a spooky story is, hoping to scare the emotionless Rick for once, with each tale even scarier (and sillier) than the last!

added.title: Late Night Good Morning With Uncle Grandpa
added.description: It's the Late Night Good Morning show with your host, Uncle Grandpa!

added.title: Noche de chicas Parte 1
added.description: El equipo de la Noche de Chicas decide quedarse en casa y celebrar una pijamada, pero una desconocida amenaza alienígena desciende sobre Jump City.

added.title: Noche de chicas Parte 2
added.description: Cuando Blackfire pone en marcha su plan para conquistar la Tierra, las chicas deben intentarlo todo para derrotarla.

added.title: El gran desastre
added.description: Robin pierde la memoria y comienza a pensar que Hombre Halcón es su madre.

added.title: We Are Heroes
added.description: KO struggles with his upgraded role as a member of the hero team.

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: Let's Meet Sonic
added.description: When world class hero SONIC THE HEDGEHOG visits the plaza, he teams up with KO to save the day.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: The K.O. Trap
added.description: KO, Rad, and Enid are caught in an especially devious trap.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: Planet X
added.description: When Rad returns to his home planet, he learns a shocking truth about alien society.

added.title: Blundercup
added.description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Land of the Lost Shadows
added.description: When pieces of their shadows are stolen by a shadow demon, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must travel to the Land of Lost Shadows in order to retrieve them.

added.title: Messy Bessy
added.description: Seth must clean his room and learn to be a neater person in order to keep Messy Bessy from making his life a nightmare.

added.title: Memory Foam
added.description: When a new mattress sucks away all of Pizza Steve's memories, Uncle Grandpa and the crew must find a way to get them back.

added.title: Gut Model
added.description: Muscle Man becomes a model.

added.title: Fists of Justice
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to do all of Skips' duties for the day.

added.title: Diary
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to fix a lock on Margaret's diary before she gets back from a weekend trip.

added.title: Death Bear
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to get a picture in death bear's cage to impress Margaret and Eileen.

added.title: Fuzzy Dice
added.description: Everyone wants to give Pops some fuzzy dice for his birthday.

added.title: Batalla en El Biggie Box
added.description: Ben y Billy Billions se enfrentan por un set de sumo exclusivo que se vende únicamente en el centro comercial más grande del mundo, isolo para descubrir que Simon Sez, de apenas seis años, lo compró primero! Así se desata una batalla dentro de una tienda que parece tenerlo todo excepto una salida fácil de encontrar.

added.title: Doble Hex
added.description: Mientras observan aves en el Parque Nacional Pinnacles, Gwen y Ben comienzan a competir para ver quién puede avistar más aves primero. Pero cuando el fuego del bosque interrumpe su diversión, el equipo Tennyson debe darse prisa para salvar a la población de aves y descubrir quién está detrás del fuego que crece sospechosamente: iHex!

added.title: Ben una y otra vez
added.description: Cuando los esfuerzos de Billy Billiones por tallar su cara en el Monte Rushmore con un láser se ven frustrados por Ben, el malcriado multimillonario se concentra en sacar a Ben del Omnitrix. Pero cuando, por accidente, abre una grieta espacio-temporal, ambos deben navegar con cuidado por otra línea de tiempo si quieren regresar al presente.

added.title: Vuela Dron
added.description: Ben y Gwen se enfrentan en una guerra de avioncitos de papel sumamente competitiva. Pero cuando unos drones con tecnología alienígena bombardean el Rustbucket, los primos deben trabajar juntos para derribar el ataque aéreo y descubrir quién está detrás de eso: iVilgax, el conquistador extraterrestre!

added.title: Tiempo de Sonar
added.description: Después de una serie de pesadillas recurrentes que afectan su sueño, Ben se niega a contarles a Max y Gwen lo que le molesta. Pero una vez que se dan cuenta de que el propio Zombozo está detrás de las pesadillas, Ben debe aceptar la ayuda de Max y Gwen si quieren ponerle fin al terror.

added.title: Atrapados en la torre
added.description: Durante un divertido espectáculo de fuegos artificiales, Unikitty y Master Frown quedan atrapados en el cuerno del castillo luego de que ella lo sorprende tratando de arruinar sus fuegos artificiales.

added.title: Entrega especial
added.description: Después de ser interrumpida por Bim Bom durante su canción matutina, una furiosa Unikitty sigue el consejo de sus amigos y escribe sus sentimientos en una carta con la intención de quedársela, pero la envía accidentalmente. La banda sale en una salvaje persecución de los servicios postales del Unireino para evitar que la irrespetuosa carta llegue a Bim Bom y hiera sus sentimientos.

added.title: Cuentos de miedo 2
added.description: Es Halloween de nuevo y la banda trata de contar aterradoras historias a un grupo de niños que piden dulces.

added.title: El Club Salchicha
added.description: Perricornio está decidido a convertirse en el rey de los hot dogs y se une al Club Salchicha, una competencia clandestina de comer hot dogs.

added.title: Nuestras Cosas
added.description: Después de jugar (muy mal) un partido informal de baloncesto, los Osos van a buscar las cosas que dejaron al costado de la cancha iy descubren que se las robaron! Corren por toda la ciudad en busca de sus cosas y terminan resolviendo un caso increíble en el camino.

added.title: Mushroom Menace
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman wants the Warriors For Hire to defend her giant pumpkin home from the dreaded Smashroom Mushroom, but Vambre and Prohyas can't complete their mission without help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword!

added.title: El Equipo Perfecto
added.description: A Cebollín le preocupa que su relación con Manzana corra peligro cuando un gato callejero entra en su vida.

added.title: Video Viral
added.description: Los Osos creen que son capaces de convertirse en estrellas en un video viral, pero cuando Nom-Nom decide que eso no va a suceder, Pardo se mete en la limosina del koala con el objetivo de hacerlo cambiar de opinión.

added.title: The Mystery of Loch-Mess
added.description: The Warriors are sent on a mission to Loch Mess to locate missing deliverymen only to find themselves captured as pets for the giant piggy Queen Porcina.

added.title: Camion De Comida
added.description: Los Osos inauguran un camión de comida porque están decepcionados con las opciones de comida que tienen disponibles. Con la intención de fomentar el negocio, empiezan a venderles su comida a animales... hasta que los animales se vuelven un poco locos.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe pasa tiempo con los Osos con el objetivo de investigarlos para una presentación que tiene que hacer pronto. Pero cuando los Osos le dan un vistazo a su informe aburrido, deciden ponerle un poco de emoción con datos exagerados sobre sí mismos y su estilo de vida.

added.title: El Dia Divertido de Falafel
added.description: Cuando Falafel decide empacar sus cosas e ir a la ciudad, Manzana y Cebollín deben convencerlo de quedarse.

added.title: Case Clothed
added.description: Princess Zange hires the Warriors to be her secret service for the afternoon to go shopping, but the looting pirates of Keelhaul Cove make fashion makeovers nearly impossible to manage.

added.title: La Cita De Panda
added.description: Cuando una vendedora del Mercado de Granjeros (LUCY) le pone a Panda una inyección antialérgica que lo revive luego de una reacción alérgica, el Oso se despierta en los brazos de su chica soñada. Panda trata de conquistar a esta mujer de ensueño, pero sus hermanos y sus propias inseguridades se entrometen en el camino.

added.title: 4 a 1
added.description: El temor de Cebollín a las multitudes amenaza el éxito de su equipo de baloncesto.

added.title: Cleanliness Is Next to Grupliness
added.description: Grup has been stinking up the entire town of Rhyboflaven, but no matter how the Warriors try to lead the little dragon to water, they can't make him bathe!

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Working for Scales
added.description: Princess Zange is sick and requires a dinosaur scale for a tea remedy, but King Rexxtopher is fiercely against the Warriors stepping foot inside his Dinosaur Kingdom to get it.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Toyman takes over the Justice League and turns them into avatars in a diabolical video game.

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he to short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Trick or Threat
added.description: Four kids in Justice League costumes are trick or treating on Halloween when they investigate a spooky house. As dangers befalls them inside, they come to realize that maybe they're not kids at all, but real Justice Leaguers under a spell.

added.title: Hat Trick
added.description: When Felix Faust steals Zatanna's magical top hat, the Justice League must help retrieve it before the evil wizard can use it to create a magic portal, releasing the demon Ghast.

added.title: Plastic Man Saves the World
added.description: Plastic Man feels shuffled off to the side as the Justice League battles Brainiac so he takes it upon himself to infiltrate the alien's ship on his own and thwart the villain's plans.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: Rage of the Red Lanterns
added.description: Chased by the Red Lanterns, Lobo seeks sanctuary with the Justice League. As the League attempts to stave off the Red Lanterns, Lobo reveals the real reason he wants shelter in the Watchtower, he wants access to a powerful space weapon being held by our heroes.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: Bedside Manners
added.description: After a nasty spill lands Belson in a full body cast, Clarence pays his bedridden friend a visit at the hospital, but what Clarence thinks will cheer him up might actually drive Belson totally crazy!

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: Food Around the Corner
added.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Chalmers Santiago
added.description: While Clarence spends a lazy Saturday playing 8-bit adventure game Dragon's Cusp, Mary asks him to return some mail to the guy across the street Chalmers Santiago, whom they've never seen. Clarence makes it his mission to befriend the mysterious neighbor, only to find out it's someone he knows quite well.

added.title: Fideito
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben seguir teniendo la onda suficiente para aparecer en el video musical de su rapero favorito.

added.title: Dia de Intercambio
added.description: Cuando los héroes creen que la vida del otro es más sencilla, intercambian sus papeles.

added.title: Conozcan a Tanya Keys
added.description: Cuando Tanya Keys, la cazadora de recompensas, llega a la ciudad para atrapar a Colosal, Mao Mao y Adorabat son los encargados de salvar a su amigo... aunque se haya metido en asuntos ilegales.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
added.description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

added.title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
added.description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: El cuarto oscuro
added.description: Tras ser rechazado por un club de fotografía, Val intenta conseguir una foto del legendario Chupacabra para demostrar su valor.

added.title: El Coleccionista
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic pierde una de las preciadas monedas de Val, Val hace un trato con un misterioso coleccionista de antigüedades para reemplazarla, pero el trato tiene consecuencias terribles.

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 1
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 2
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: Be a Team
added.description: Mr. Gar brings in some team building experts to help KO, Enid and Rad.

added.title: Point to the Plaza
added.description: When a Gloop infestation takes over the plaza, Point arrives to contain the situation.

added.title: Let's Watch the Boxmore Show
added.description: Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.

added.title: TKO's House
added.description: TKO is getting restless.

added.title: Let's Be Heroes
added.description: When KO tags along with his mom to work, he discovers the convenience store next door is his key to becoming a great hero.

added.title: You're Everybody's Sidekick
added.description: KO sets out to prove to Enid that being helpful is rewarding by helping people all around the Lakewood Plaza Turbo.

added.title: We Messed Up
added.description: KO, Rad and Enid accidentally break one of Mr. Gar's prized possessions!

added.title: You're Level 100!
added.description: When KO finally gets a Pow Card, he finds out he's level 100, instantly making him a celebrity and the idol of everyone.

added.title: Just Be a Pebble
added.description: KO eats a piece of new candy at Gar's that makes him giant.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Clarence for President
added.description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

added.title: Clarence Wendle and the Eye of Coogan
added.description: Clarence and other students find the crusty old journal of Coogan filled with clues leading to a mysterious treasure. Clarence spearheads the team of treasure hunters to journey through the perils of Aberdale seeking the lost Eye of Coogan.

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Birthday Bash/Too Pooped to Puff
added.description: Birthday Bash: It's the girls birthday and some special presents have arrived from the girls' main enemies. Can they destroy these evil gifts without destroying their party?/Too Pooped to Puff: The girls become exhausted when the town begins to over use them. They go on strike and end up teaching the townspeople how to fend for themselves.

added.title: Paste Makes Waste/Ice Sore
added.description: Paste Makes Waste: When Buttercup's taunting turns paste-eating classmate Elmer Sglue into a destructive Paste Monster, she gets out of a sticky situation by doing something against her tough nature, apologizing./Ice Sore: During a heat wave, Blossom discovers that she has a new power: ice breath. But when she doesn't use her new gift wisely, she gets a chilly reception from her sisters.

added.title: Bliss Reminisce
added.description: The Girls learn Bliss' backstory from the Professor, Mojo Jojo, and Bliss herself.

added.title: Breaking Bliss
added.description: When Bliss struggles to control her powers an evil force arises to take advantage.

added.title: The Stayover
added.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
added.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

added.title: The Squashening
added.description: To escape a monster, the girls have to tell him a scary story.

added.title: Collection Infection
added.description: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: For the Love of Narwhal
added.description: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Fixing a Flonk
added.description: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

added.title: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
added.description: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

added.title: Dizzy
added.description: M and R help Pops get over his fear of public speaking.

added.title: Brain Eraser
added.description: Benson gets demoted and has to work with Mordecai and Rigby.

added.title: Benson Be Gone
added.description: Mordecai sees Pops naked and goes on a quest to unsee what he has seen.

added.title: But I Have a Receipt
added.description: When a bad game ruins game night, M & R attempt to return it to a not-so-pleasant store manager.

added.title: Do Me a Solid
added.description: Mordecai owes Rigby big time when he agrees to go on a double date with him.

added.title: The Power
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby find a mysterious keyboard that allows them to do anything they want, including accidently sending Benson to the moon.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Prank Callers
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try and prank the Master Prank Caller to be the best prank callers. The MPC sends them back to 1982.

added.title: Mordecai and the Rigbys
added.description: After lying about having an awesome band, Mordecai and Rigby must get help from their future selves in order to learn how to play in time for the battle of the bands.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: Washington B.C.
added.description: Ben must use the Omnitrix to transform into alien heroes to battle Dr. Amino and his transmorphed dinosaurs running rampant in Washington DC.

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Mr. Smoothy's
added.description: The Plumbers' resident geniuses, Blukic and Driba set off to find some smoothies meanwhile Ben and Rook try to stop Trombipulor from gaining the source of absolute power.

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: El Pacto
added.description: Gumball y el director Brown hacen un pacto: le contarán sus problemas a la novia del otro.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Titanes Casuales en Accion
added.description: La Junta de Autoridades de Superhéroes establece un código de vestimenta que lleva a los Titanes a implementar el Martes Informal.

added.title: La pregunta
added.description: Steven les muestra a unas gemas citadinas cómo vivían los vaqueros.

added.title: Reunificados
added.description: Steven reúne a todos para un evento especial.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: Con tantos cambios en su vida, Steven intenta encontrar su lugar en el mundo.

added.title: Juntos Solos
added.description: Steven organiza una fiesta para reunir a su familia.

added.title: Escapismo
added.description: Steven usa sus poderes psíquicos para conseguir ayuda.

added.title: Cambia de Parecer
added.description: Steven se enfrenta al mayor desafío de su vida.

added.title: Los Jovenes Titanes Rugen
added.description: Los Titanes se indignan cuando su caricatura favorita es reiniciada, así que idean un plan para sacar al nuevo show del aire.

added.title: El metro
added.description: Luego de perder el tren, los Osos quedan varados en una plataforma del subterráneo. Pero mientras esperan, se desafían a recuperar algunos objetos perdidos.

added.title: El amigo de panda
added.description: Panda usa una aplicación para encontrar a un amigo con el que tenga más cosas en común. Muy pronto, las cosas dan un giro negativo cuando el nuevo amigo se vuelve demasiado posesivo.

added.title: Vecinos
added.description: Algunos vecinos nuevos arman campamento junto a la cueva de los Osos. A Panda y a Polar les encanta, pero Pardo cree que no tienen buenas intenciones.

added.title: Planeta osos
added.description: Un documental sobre la naturaleza sigue a los Osos durante su rutina normal, que incluye un viaje a la tienda de comestibles.

added.title: Cambio de Temporada
added.description: Cuando nuestros héroes regresan de sus vacaciones, K.O. se horroriza al descubrir que las cosas cambiaron.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Trabajando en Equipo
added.description: El Sr. Gar trae a un equipo de expertos en construcción para que ayuden a K.O., Enid y Rad.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Veamos el Show de Boxmore
added.description: Nuestros héroes descubren que las grabaciones de la cámara de seguridad de Boxmore son la cosa más divertida del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Apointa a la Plaza
added.description: Cuando la plaza se infesta de pegote, P.O.I.N.T. llega para contener la situación.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Momento Perfecto
added.description: Cuando Halcondrilo admite su amor por la Dra. Fox, Unikitty y sus amigos se convierten en sus gurús del amor para ayudarlo a confesar sus sentimientos por ella. Por desgracia, los grandes planes de Unikitty para el momento perfecto del amor lo complican todo.

added.title: Sensei Halcondrilo
added.description: En una misión de rutina, Halcondrilo encuentra algunas ardillas indefensas que lo siguen como abrojos. El ave guardaespaldas decide convertirse en Sensei para enseñar a los jóvenes sus destrezas de guerrero. Pero Unikitty teme que su entrenamiento sea demasiado intenso. ¿El estilo de vida de Halcondrilo en el que todo es trabajo y no hay tiempo para el juego hará que las ardillitas sobrepasen sus límites?

added.title: Aparato P.L.O.T.
added.description: Cuando el aburrimiento en el castillo llega a niveles peligrosamente altos, la Dra. Fox convenientemente introduce su dispositivo P.L.O.T. Cuando se pulsa, este dispositivo altera la realidad para hacerla más emocionante. Richard advierte que esto puede ser peligroso, pero nadie escucha. No pasará mucho tiempo antes de que se demuestre que tiene razón y la vida en el castillo se vuelva peligrosamente emocionante.

added.title: Bip
added.description: Para ayudar a combatir los sentimientos negativos, Unikitty ha instalado detectores de malas vibraciones en todo el castillo. Pero pronto, la molesta alarma de los detectores llena los pasillos, iy nadie puede encontrar la fuente de las malas vibraciones ni apagar el sonido! Parece que alguien no está reconociendo su propio mal humor. ¿Se darán cuenta los amigos de quién es la persona que guarda su negatividad en secreto, o perderán la cabeza por la locura de la alarma?

added.title: Lazer Tag

added.title: Eres El Asistente De Todos

added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Eres Nivel 100

added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Amigo roca

Incentivado a ""hacer más amigos"", Puppycorn no puede encontrar a alguien con quien sienta afinidad, hasta que sigue el consejo de Unikitty y decide literalmente hacer un nuevo amigo con las mejores partes de sus amigos. Esto no irá bien.

added.title: Caos en la cocina
added.description: Después de lesionarse en su lugar de trabajo, Richard no puede hacer sus tareas de criado. Unikitty y los demás se encargan de una simple tarea: limpiar la cocina. Esta actividad increíblemente aburrida es un desafío para nuestros héroes, que buscan todas las formas posibles de no hacerla. ¿Serán capaces de alcanzar esta meta y traer de regreso a Richard?

added.title: Se Una Piedrita

added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Fiesta de cumpleanos

Para recuperarlo, Unikitty y Puppycorn tendrán que aventurarse en la tierra más deprimente de la historia: iFrown Town! ¿Conseguirán recuperar el deseo de cumpleaños de manos de Frown antes de que su deseo (y todos los deseos) desaparezcan para siempre?

added.title: Senor Casero

Preocupado, Brock invita a Unikitty y a la pandilla para que los ayuden. En lugar de hacer lo que los chicos quieren en su casa, Unikitty procede a hacer lo que ella quiere. Al darse cuenta de su error, devuelve el apartamento a su antiguo estado asqueroso, pero ahora Frown y Brock están en peligro de desalojo de nuevo. Deben aliarse a Unikitty y la banda para luchar contra el malvado casero y salvar su hogar.

added.title: Historias de miedo
added.description: Durante la fiesta de Halloween de la banda, iUnikitty descubre que Rick no le teme a nada! Para contagiarle el espíritu festivo, Unikitty cuenta sus propias ideas de lo que es una historia espeluznante, con la esperanza de asustar al inconmovible de Rick por una vez. iPero cada cuento es aún más espeluznante (y más tonto) que el anterior!
